mdRecord.dcterms:title: Floyd Grange #761
mdRecord.dcterms:description: Newspaper image of Floyd Grange, with text under the image reading "Floyd Grange No. 760, pictured in 1937, was the first grange organized in Southwest Virginia." The second photograph is a group photograph of people in front of the grange, with their names on the back of the photograph.
mdRecord.dcterms:provenance: Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University. University Libraries
